{
  "id": "pl24",
  "type": "plotlines",
  "name": "Villain's Journey",
  "description": "An outline formula for writing villains based on the classic Hero's Journey",
  "version": "2021.10.15",
  "categories": [
    "general"
  ],
  "templateData": {
    "cards": [
      {
        "id": 8,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 9,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Ordeal, Death, Rebirth",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Act 3:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Victory is snatched away by the Hero... and the Villain is left to face the consequences. They may be destroyed, killed, banished, jailed, or convinced to turn back to the path of good. No matter the outcome, the Villain is no longer a threat as they were at the beginning of the story."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Finish the final confrontation between Villain and Hero, with the Villain failing and the Hero emerging victorious."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Outline the consequences for the Villain and what they have learned (if they are still alive)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Close the character arc of the Villain and any remaining loose threads from their story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "If part of a series, set the hook for the next installment and hint at the Villain's next diabolical plan."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "While the Villain's Journey closely mirrors the Hero's Journey, the Villain does not have a reward, a homecoming, or an opportunity to relax in a new world they have created. They have been defeated and are sent off to lick their wounds and devise another plan."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 3 makes up the final 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Ordeal, Death, Rebirth occurs around the 75% mark."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The Villain's final consequences occur around the 90% - 95% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
