      {
        "id": 2,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 3,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Call to Adventure",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Middle of Act 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The event which upset the Villain in Beat 1 becomes their Call here. For example: they may need to repair their project at all costs; avenge the death of a loved one; fight the allies that betrayed them; or feel the urge to put an evil plan into play. Villains usually do not see themselves as evil or wrong-doers; they generally see themselves as trying to right a wrong or make the world a better place. But most people do not agree with their methods or sense of reality."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Turn the displeasing event in Beat 1 into a Call to Adventure, a reason for the Villain to be thrust into the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Give the Villain a unique perspective that makes it clear they do not see themselves as evil."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Introduce the overall theme of the story and the Central Issue to be resolved."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "How will succeeding in this Journey make the Villain's world better?"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 1 makes up the first 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Call to Adventure occurs around the 10% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
